In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. proclaims September 11, 2022, as Patriot Day and National Day of Service and Remembrance. He pays tribute to the heroes and victims of the September 11, 2001 attacks and highlights the acts of heroism displayed by ordinary Americans. The president encourages Americans to observe the day with service and unity, emphasizing that it is our greatest strength. He also calls for the flag of the United States to be displayed at half-staff and for a moment of silence to honor the innocent victims. The article concludes with the official proclamation and invitation for individuals and organizations to join in the observance.